parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical shorts, resulting in fires in the steering column, engine compartment, or dashboard area, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Cracking noise when turning the key
smoke coming from under the hood
fire in the center of the engine compartment
ignition switch feels hot or warm to the touch
smoke or flames coming from the steering column or dashboard area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause electrical shorts, resulting in fires in the steering column, engine compartment, or dashboard area, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Electrical short in the wiring harness
smoke or flames coming from under the hood
fire in the center of the engine compartment
smoke or flames coming from the steering column or dashboard area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission shift lever can cause the vehicle to roll away unexpectedly, leading to accidents, property damage, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shift lever moves out of the "Park" position on its own
the vehicle rolls away without the key in the ignition
the transmission indicator shows an incorrect gear selection
the vehicle moves forward or backward without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Transmission or Throttle Control Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The vehicle may surge forward without warning, making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward without warning
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when shifting into gear
the brakes may not be effective in stopping the vehicle.
